user_uid is passed in URL

events/project/users/{user_uid} -- 
Get a count of a given user's project events;
user_uid is passed in URL

events/project/users/{user_uid}/events -- 
Get info about Project User Events for a given user's projects;
user_uid is passed in URL

events/users/{user_uid}/num -- 
Get a count of a given user's events of all types;
user_uid is passed in URL

events/personal/users/{user_uid}/num -- 
Get a count of a given user's personal events;
user_uid is passed in URL

events/project/users/{user_uid}/num -- 
Get a count of a given user's project events;
user_uid is passed in URL

events/project/users/{user_uid}/events/num -- 
Get a count of a Project User Events for a given user's projects;
user_uid is passed in URL

packages/public -- 
Get info about curated packages;
does not require sign-in

packages/types -- 
Get info about available package types;
Does not require sign-in

packages/github --
sent by GigHub webhook on trigger;
does not require sign-in

packages/all --
Get a list of all packages; 
returns nothing unless the signed in user is an admin;
Note that only the owner can see "secret_token"--for all other users it is "null" even if set in the database.

packages/{package_uuid} --
Get info about a given package; 
The package uuid is provided in the URL;
Note that only the owner can see "secret_token"--for all other users it is "null" even if set in the database.

packages --
Creates a new package with the signed-in user as the owner;
Set Package parameters in the Body.

packages/protected/{project_uuid} --
Get a list of protected packages shared with one or more given projects; 
the project uuids are provided in the URL (+ delimited);
Sharing is at the Package-Version-level;
Note that only the owner can see "secret_token"--for all other users it is "null" even if set in the database

packages/protected/{project_uuid}/num --
Get a count of protected packages shared with one or more given projects; 
the project uuids are provided in the URL (+ delimited);
Sharing is at the Package-Version-level

packages/users/{user_uuid} --
Get a list of protected packages available to a given user; 
the user uuid is provided in the URL.
Note that only the owner can see "secret_token"--for all other users it is "null" even if set in the database;
Packages returned are those with one or more versions shared with any of the user's projects

packages/users/{user_uuid}/num --
Get a count of protected packages available to a given user; 
the user uuid is provided in the URL;
Packages counted are those with one or more versions shared with any of the user's projects

packages/{package_uuid}/projects --
Get info about a the Projects a given Package is shared with; 
The package uuid is provided in the URL;
Sharing is at the Package-Version-level

packages/{package_uuid}/platforms --
Get a list of the Platforms a given Package is incompatible with; 
The package uuid is provided in the URL;
Note that this looks for records in the package_platform table with compatible_flag set to 1, but the SWAMP uses this table as an incompatibility table and only has existing records with compatible_flat set to 0.
Not used in SWAMP UI

packages/{package_uuid}/versions --
Get a list of package versions for a given Package; 
The package uuid is provided in the URL

packages/{package_uuid}/{project_uuid}/versions --
Get a list of package versions for a given Package that are shared with a given Project; 
The package_uuid  and project_uuid are provided in the URL;
Sharing is at the Package-Version-level

packages/{package_uuid} --
Edit a given package;
package_uuid is passed in URL;
Set Package parameters in the params

packages/{package_uuid} --
Delete a given package;
package_uuid is passed in URL

packages/{package_uuid}/versions --
Delete a given package;
package_uuid is passed in URL

packages/versions/dependencies --
Creates a new Dependency for a given Package Veresion for a Given Platform;
Set Dependency parameters in the Body

packages/{package_uuid}/versions/dependencies/recent --
Get a list of dependencies for the latest version of a given package;
package uuid is passed in URL

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/dependencies --
Get a list of dependencies for the a given package version;
package version uuid is passed in URL

packages/versions/dependencies/{package_version_dependency_id} --
Edit the dependency list for a package version for a platform version;
package_version_dependency_id is passed in URL;
Edited info is passed in the params

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/dependencies/{platform_version_uuid} --
delete all dependencies for a given package version and platform version;
package_version_uuid and platform_version_uuid are passed in URL;
Returns the number of records deleted

packages/versions/upload --
Uploads a file for creation of a new Package or Package Version;
Select the file in Body

packages/versions/upload --
Downlaods a file for creation of a new Package or Package Version;
Select the file in Body

packages/versions/upload --
Clones and archives a file for creation of a new Package or Package Version;
Select the file in Body

packages/versions --
Creates a new package version;
Set Package Version parameters in the Body;
Used in SWAMP UI to add a new version to an existing package, in which case it is followed by the ...add post

packages/versions/store --
Creates a new package version and moves the temporary upload file to the permanant storage location;
Set Package Version parameters in the Body.
Get package_path by combining returned destination_path and file_name from the upload post;
Used by SWAMP UI when creating a new package

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/add -- 
Moves the temporary file for a new package version to the permanent location and updates the database record;
Get package_path by combining returned destination_path and file_name from the upload post;
Used in SWAMP UI for adding a new version to an existing package following the creation post

packages/versions/new/root --
Get a the root directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post

packages/versions/new/contains --
Check if a given file is in a given directory of the temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory you wish to check;
Set filname in params with the name of the file you are checking for;
Set recursive in params to true or false

packages/versions/new/file-types --
Get a list of file types and corresponding counts in a directory of the temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Package Path for the new package

packages/versions/new/file-list --
Get a list of the files in a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory for which you want to view contents

packages/versions/new/file-tree --
Get the file tree for a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory for which you want to view contents

packages/versions/new/directory-list --
Get a list of the directories in a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory for which you want to view contents

packages/versions/new/directory-tree --
Get the Directory tree for a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory for which you want to view contents

packages/versions/new/build-system --
Get build system based on the contents of a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set source_path in params with the Archive Path to the directory from which you want to view get build info;
Set package_type_id based on selected package_type

packages/versions/new/build-info --
Get build information based on the contents of a given directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set source_path in params with the Archive Path to the directory from which you want to view get build info;
Set package_type_id based on selected package_type

packages/versions/new/ruby-gem-info --
Get Ruby Gem infor from a specific directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory from which you want to get Ruby Gem info

packages/versions/new/python-wheel-info --
Get Python Wheel info from a specific directory of a temp archive for a new package version;
Set package_path in params by combining the destination_path and file returned on the store post;
Set dirname in params with the Archive Path to the directory from which you want to get Python Wheel info

packages/versions/build-system/check --
Performs a check of build parameters based on the files existing in the Package Version Archive;
Set Package Build Information parameters in the Body

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/root --
Get a the root directory of the archive for a given package_version;
package_version_uid is passed in URL

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/contains --
Check if a given file is in a given directory of the archive for a given package_version;
package_version_uid is passed in URL;
file to search for, directory to search, and whether to search recursively are included in params

packages/versions/{package_version_uuid}/file-types --
