users/validate --
Check if an email or username can be used; 
pass email, username, and/or password in body

users --
Register a new user; 
pass user info in body (first_name, last_name, username, password, email, class_code; 
Does not handle email verification: call POST /verifications subsequently for this.

verifications/resend -- 
Re-send an email to verify email address of registered but unverified user; 
pass username and password in body

verifications/{verification_key} -- 
Delete the email verification record matching the given verification key (the key is provided in the URL in the verification email);
This is not used in the WebUI, and there is no use case for deleting email verifications (status changes are handled without need for deletion).

password_resets -- 
Send an email to reset the password for a given user; 
pass username or email in the body to determine user

password_resets/{password_reset_uuid}/{password_reset_nonce} -- 
Get info about a password reset key; 
pass reset uuid and nonce in URL;
nonce is provided only in the email sent to the user on requesting a password reset

password_resets/reset -- 
Reset a password with a given password reset key; 
pass reset key and new password in params

{{csa}}/login -- 
sign in to SWAMP;
pass username and password in body

users/email/request-username --
Send a "forgotten username" email; 
pass email in body

oauth2 --
attempt to sign in with info from an oauth2 site;
code and state passed as params as retrieved from the redirect route

oauth2/link --
link an existing SWAMP account to a third-party oauth2 account using the given SWAMP credentials and an oauth2_id;
pass credentails in the body

